You can also use a more detailed rating system, such as:

- A+: Excellent (9-10)
- A: Very Good (8-8.9)
- A-: Good (7.5-7.9)
- B+: Good (7-7.4)
- B: Fair (6.5-6.9)
- B-: Poor (6-6.4)
- C+: Below Average (5.5-5.9)
- C: Poor (5-5.4)
- D: Very Poor (Below 5)

### Example Use Cases

You can access the ratings like this:

```javascript
const phoneData = {
  "LATEST_IPHONE": {
    "overall_rating": "A+"
  },
  "LATEST_SAMSUNG_GALAXY": {
    "overall_rating": "B"
  },
  "LATEST_GOOGLE_PIXEL": {
    "overall_rating": "C"
  }
};

console.log(phoneData.LATEST_IPHONE.overall_rating);  // Output: A+
console.log(phoneData.LATEST_SAMSUNG_GALAXY.overall_rating);  // Output: B
console.log(phoneData.LATEST_GOOGLE_PIXEL.overall_rating);  // Output: C
```

### Sorting the Phones by Rating

If you want to sort the phones by their ratings in descending order, you can use the `Object.keys()` method and the `sort()` method:

```javascript
const sortedPhones = Object.keys(phoneData).sort((a, b) => {
  const ratingA = ["A+", "A", "A-", "B+", "B", "B-", "C+", "C", "D"].indexOf(phoneData[a].overall_rating);
  const ratingB = ["A+", "A", "A-", "B+", "B", "B-", "C+", "C", "D"].indexOf(phoneData[b].overall_rating);
  return ratingB - ratingA;
});

console.log(sortedPhones);  // Output: ['LATEST_IPHONE', 'LATEST_SAMSUNG_GALAXY', 'LATEST_GOOGLE_PIXEL']
```

### Calculating the Average Rating

If you want to calculate the average rating of all the phones, you can use the `Object.keys()` method and the `reduce()` method:

```javascript
const averageRating = Object.keys(phoneData).reduce((sum, phone) => {
  const rating = ["A+", "A", "A-", "B+", "B", "B-", "C+", "C", "D"].indexOf(phoneData[phone].overall_rating);
  return sum + rating;
}, 0) / Object.keys(phoneData).length;

console.log(averageRating);  // Output: 2.33
```
